ical MBHB\ndriving the GWB signal come from redshifts around $0.3$, with total masses of a\nfew times $10^9\\,M_\\odot$, and in host galaxies with very large stellar masses.\nEven without GWB detections, our results can be connected to observations of\ndual AGN to constrain binary evolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Jun 2016 20:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 5 Oct 2016 17:58:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-06"}
